data.description: Welcome to your new home with endless potential! This spacious property on 908 Taseschee Dr in Sebring, FL is a hidden gem that offers the perfect opportunity to create a mother-in-law suite or additional living space to suit your unique needs.  Situated. this charming house provides a solid foundation for your creative vision.   The distinctive layout lends itself perfectly to the addition of a mother-in-law suite, offering a separate living area that provides privacy and independence for extended family members or potential rental income. Imagine the possibilities of having a self-contained space complete with a bedroom, bathroom, kitchenette, and living area, all under the same roof.  The property itself offers ample space for expansion, including a large backyard that can accommodate the new addition with ease. Embrace the Florida lifestyle by creating an outdoor oasis for relaxation or entertaining, including a sunny patio, a lush garden.  Conveniently located in Sebring, this home is surrounded by a variety of amenities, including shopping centers, restaurants, parks, and entertainment options. Enjoy the comfort of a peaceful neighborhood while still being in close proximity to everything you need for everyday living.Don't miss out on this incredible opportunity to transform this home into a lucrative investment or a haven for multi-generational living. With a little imagination and the vision for potential, this property on 908 Taseschee Dr is your chance to create the perfect mother-in-law suite and make this house truly your own.  Contact me today to schedule a showing and let your creativity run wild as you envision the possibilities this property holds!LOOKING FOR THE PERFECT FAMILY HOME??? Look no further, a Newly renovated house with 3 Bedrooms 2 bathrooms, updated Kitchen and bath, new fence, new A/C, and new Shed convey. Great location only one block from Lake Jackson, Near the charming Downtown Circle, shopping, Restaurants, Schools, and medical facilities. No HOA no fees!!! It's definitely worth taking a look at.
